item.title: San Francisco Cheezburger Launch Party is Tonight!
item.dc:creator: tofuburger
item.description: epic fail-San Francisco Cheezburger Launch Party is Tonight!
item.content:encoded:
Our Cheezburger Book launch party is tonight! If you’re in the San Francisco area, we expect all of your FAILers to come on by! We’re celebrating the book launches of FAIL Blog’s new book FAIL Nation: A Visual Romp through the World of Epic Fails, ICHC’s new book How To Take Over Teh Wurld: A LOLCat Guide 2 Winning, and GraphJam’s new book GRAPH OUT LOUD.

What: Free Cheezburger Book Launch Party with lots of books, FAILs, and cheezburgers!

Where: Citizen Space Inc.: 425 2nd Street, Suite 100, San Francisco

When: Wednesday, October 28, 6:30-9pm

Bring cans of cat food, cat toys, blankets or make a donation on site to the San Francisco SPCA, and you will be entered into a raffle to win an awesome new iPod Nano with video!

See you all tonight!

item.title: Come to the Cheezburger Book Launch Party in San Francisco!
item.dc:creator: tofuburger
item.description: epic fail: Come to the Cheezburger Book Launch Party in San Francisco!
item.content:encoded:
Hey San Francisco FAILers! We’re hosting a Cheezburger Book Launch Party/Happy Hour in San Francisco! Join us as we celebrate the book launches of FAIL Blog’s new book FAIL Nation: A Visual Romp through the World of Epic Fails, ICHC’s new book How To Take Over Teh Wurld: A LOLCat Guide 2 Winning, and GraphJam’s new book GRAPH OUT LOUD.

We’ll have tons of books and Happy Cats available and Ben Huh, CEO of the Cheezburger Network, will be there in person to call our your FAILs and sign books.

Its free to attend and there will be plenty of drinks, cheezburgers, and fun! We’re also teaming up with the San Francisco SPCA, and guests who bring cans of cat food, cat toys, blankets or make a donation on site will be entered into a raffle to win an awesome new iPod Nano with video!

Where: Citizen Space Inc.: 425 2nd Street, Suite 100, San Francisco

When: Wednesday, October 28, 6:30-9pm

See you all there!
